.TH SP-CHECK-INVARIANTS 1 "Spherepop Tools" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sp-check-invariants \- perturbation checks for claimed invariants (statement-level)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sp-check-invariants
.RB [ \-i " invariant" ]
.RB [ \-p " P1|P2|P3" ]
.RB [ \-o " out.txt" ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
sp-check-invariants produces a small report about whether a claimed invariant
appears stable under stylized perturbation classes.
.PP
This tool is not a system diagnostic. It does not access external systems.
It operates on the invariant statement itself.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-i " text"
Invariant statement to assess.
.TP
.BI \-p " class"
Perturbation class: P1, P2, or P3.
.TP
.BI \-o " file"
Write report to file (default: ./invariants.txt).
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success, non-zero on error.
.SH SEE ALSO
sp-probe-goodhart(1), sp-drift-metrics(1)

